yart v0.1.4 (Release date: 2017-12-06)
===========

Changes:

* More formatting options such as margins, paper size are included in the yaml header.






yart v0.1.3 (Release date: 2017-12-06)
===========

Changes:

* The date is now set to today as default.
* New command `\ts` as a shorthand for `\thinspace`.





yart v0.1.2 (Release date: 2017-11-30)
===========

Changes:

* Update TeX template to make many YAML variables optional.
* New yaml variables: "UP_title" and "UP_subtitle" to render the title and the subtitle in UPpercase (or not)
* quotation marks are rendered using `\usepackage{csquotes}` thus providing support for quotations of different languages
* block quotation can now be changed to a shaded field via the yaml attribute `shaded_quote`
* line break for long urls in the references



